hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: i'm fine good work wvu medicine children's gala He reminds me of Howard Hughes, without all the nasty OCD issues (at least, not yet). He makes big ideas seem doable, and then does them. He’s 4 for 4 so far (PayPal, Tesla, SpaceX, SolarCity), so that gives me confidence he could at least pull off a demonstrator. It does have a bit of 70s sci-fi halo around it (maybe even Futurama) and he’d likely admit as much, but still, it’s daring and dream-like. I think he understimates the pushback on a hundreds of miles of 100-foot tall pylons but who knows, maybe that could be reduced to 20 feet or something more tolerable.
